The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 03 February is 36,874 (4,267.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 29 January, there were 2,245 new confirmed cases (259.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 22 January, there were 3,133 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 28% (888 fewer cases).
